-- models/intermediate/int_deduped_returns.sql
-- Deduplicate returns to one approved return per item
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        return_id,
        item_id,
        return_date,
        reason,
        status,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY item_id
            ORDER BY return_date ASC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_returns') }}
)
SELECT
    return_id,
    item_id,
    return_date,
    reason,
    status
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

```sql
-- models/fact/fct_return_rates_by_category.sql
-- Calculate product return rates by category
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        COALESCE(c.name, '(unknown)') AS category_name,
        COUNT(DISTINCT oi.item_id) AS total_items_sold,
        COUNT(DISTINCT r.item_id) AS total_items_returned,
        CAST(COUNT(DISTINCT r.item_id) AS DECIMAL(10,2)) / NULLIF(COUNT(DISTINCT oi.item_id), 0) AS return_rate
    FROM {{ ref('stg_order_items') }} oi
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_products') }} p
        ON p.product_id = oi.product_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_categories') }} c
        ON c.category_id = p.category_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_deduped_returns') }} r
        ON r.item_id = oi.item_id
    GROUP BY
        COALESCE(c.name, '(unknown)')
)
SELECT
    category_name,
    total_items_sold,
    total_items_returned,
    return_rate
FROM source
